snippet: The final vote of the City Council, 41 to 1, was an anticlimactic conclusion to a raucous public process over months in which many residents bitterly criticized the plan.
abstract: New York City Council overwhelmingly approves bitterly protested plan allowing developer Jamestown Properties to build two office buildings atop Chelsea Market.
lead_paragraph: The final vote of the City Council, 41 to 1, was an anticlimactic conclusion to a raucous public process over months in which many residents bitterly criticized the plan.

headline.seo: New York Approves Office Buildings Atop Chelsea Market
headline.main: City Approves Office Buildings Atop Chelsea Market
headline.print_headline: City Approves Office Buildings Atop Chelsea Market
